  "body": "Since upgrading to React 15.0.1, when rendering `<select>` with optgroups, the value is not set on the DOM correctly. The first option will always get picked.\n\n``` js\n// Renders with \"Yes\" selected, I expect \"Maybe\"\n  <select value={3}>\n    <optgroup label=\"One\">\n    <option value={1}>Yes</option>\n    </optgroup>\n    <optgroup label=\"Two\">\n    <option value={2}>No</option>\n    </optgroup>\n    <optgroup label=\"Three\">\n    <option value={3}>Maybe</option>\n    </optgroup>\n  </select>\n```\n## Examples\n\n[React 15.0.1 Fiddle (broken)](http://jsbin.com/madesikinu/3/edit?html,js,output)\n[React 0.14.7 Fiddle (works)](http://jsbin.com/zofayocijo/1/edit?html,js,output)\n[React 15.0.1 without optgroup Fiddle (works)](http://jsbin.com/madesikinu/5/edit?html,js,output)\n## Environment\n\nOS X 10.11.4\nSafari Version 9.1 (11601.5.17.1)\nChrome Version 49.0.2623.110 (64-bit)\nFirefox 45.0.1\n\n_Edit: I also noticed that the same behavior occurs when using `defaultValue`._\n",
